> 
> http://www.btlmex.com/index.asp?PageAction=VIEWPROD&ProdID=212

from the picture it sure looks like it's still a mech only advance.
You picked the correct part. You would still have hesitation with the
electronic setup (it just might burn cleaner)
> 
> So my question is, did I buy the wrong thing? Anybody have experience with 
> the electronic conversion kit? I wish I had seen this sooner, I'd have just 
> spent the extra $20 or so for this instead of just the better points 
> distributor. Does this have a good advance curve, or does that even apply 
> to an electronic ignition? Since this is computer controlled will it just 
> always find the best time to spark?

I'd use the svda and put some sort of points replacement in. I use the
pertronix, but there was a recent discussion on the list about some
other options. (member of the I hate dealing with points club)

